 2016  }}</ref><ref name=\"gamasutra noms\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/274107/Life_is_Strange_leads_Games_for_Change_Awards_noms.php |title=Life is Strange leads Games for Change Awards noms |first=Chris |last=Kerr |date=2 June 2016 |work=[[Gamasutra]] |accessdate=2 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603144631/http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/274107/Life_is_Strange_leads_Games_for_Change_Awards_noms.php |archivedate=3 June 2016  }}</ref>\n|- valign=\"center\"\n| Most Significant Impact\n| {{Won}}\n|- valign=\"center\"\n| Best Gameplay\n| {{Nom}}\n|- valign=\"center\"\n| Most Innovative\n| {{Nom}}\n|- valign=\"center\"\n| [[Japan Game Awards]]\n| Game Designers Award\n| {{Won}}\n| <ref name=\"jga\">{{cite web |url=http://awards.cesa.or.jp/en/press/pdf/160915_02.pdf |title=Game Designers Award 2016 |date=15 September 2016 |website=[[Computer Entertainment Supplier's Association|CESA]] |accessdate=28 September 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161014030338/http://awards.cesa.or.jp/en/press/pdf/160915_02.pdf |archivedate=14 October 2016  }}</ref>\n|- valign=\"center\"\n| [[Apple Inc.|Apple]]'s Best of 2016\n| Game of the Year\n| {{Won}}\n| <ref name=\"apple\">{{cite web |url=http://www.develop-online.net/press-releases/life-is-strange-trade-wins-game-of-the-year-in-apple-rsquo-s-best-of-2016/0227552 |title=Life Is Strange wins Game of the Year in Apple's Best of 2016 |first=Rajitha |last=Ratnam |date=8 December 2016 |website=[[Develop (magazine)|Develop]] |publisher=[[NewBay Media]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220103340/http://www.develop-online.net/press-releases/life-is-strange-trade-wins-game-of-the-year-in-apple-rsquo-s-best-of-2016/0227552 |archivedate=20 December 2016 |access-date=12 December 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|- valign=\"center\"\n| [[Steam Awards]]\n| \"I'm Not Crying, There's Something In My Eye\"\n| {{Nominated}}\n| <ref name=\"not crying\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vg247.com/2016/12/20/every-game-nominated-for-the-steam-awards/ |title=Every game nominated for the Steam Awards |first=Sherif |last=Saed |date=20 December 2016 |website=[[VG247]] |publisher=[[VG247|Videogaming247 Ltd]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161230003140/https://www.vg247.com/2016/12/20/every-game-nominated-for-the-steam-awards/ |archivedate=30 December 2016  }}</ref><ref name=\"or am I\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/valve-announces-winners-of-first-ever-steam-awards/ |title=Valve announces winners of first ever Steam Awards |first=Tom |last=Sykes |date=1 January 2017 |website=[[PC Gamer]] |publisher=[[Future plc]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102080237/http://www.pcgamer.com/valve-announces-winners-of-first-ever-steam-awards/ |archivedate=2 January 2017  }}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Legacy==\nAfter ''Life Is Strange'' achieved financial and commercial success, Dontnod Entertainment started to become more prominent in the video game industry; publishers pursued the studio for the first time, whereas they previously had to pursue publishers themselves. CEO Oskar Guilbert said that the game saved his company financially after the mediocre sales of ''[[Remember Me (video game)|Remember Me]]''.<ref name=\"solicited success\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/how-life-is-strange-changed-dontnod/0174354 |title=How Life is Strange changed Dontnod |first=Christopher |last=Dring |date=25 October 2016 |website=[[MCV (magazine)|MCV]] |accessdate=25 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026080029/http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/how-life-is-strange-changed-dontnod/0174354 |archivedate=26 October 2016  }}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Square Enix sponsored its own \"Everyday Heroes\" photography contest, inspired by the game, offering a {{USD|10,000}} scholarship for the winning entry.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/2016/1/26/10834900/life-is-strange-everyday-heroes-scholarship-fund-contest | title = Life is Strange sponsors actual Everyday Heroes photo contest | first = Allegra | last = Frank  |date = 26 January 2016 | accessdate = 1 October 2018 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]}}</ref> Square Enix also coordinated with Parent Advocacy Coalition for Educational Rights (PACER) to support an anti-bullying initiative based on themes within the game<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/2016/1/13/10763900/life-is-strange-everyday-heroes-pacer-national-bullying-prevention | title = Life is Strange charity challenge asks 'everyday heroes' to prevent bullying | first = Allegra | last =Frank | date = 13 January 2016 | accessdate = 1 October 2018 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] }}</ref> and donated a total amount of $25,000.<ref>{{Cite tweet|number=691672571826298880|user=LifeIsStrange|title=Thanks to all your #everydayheroes stories we will be donating $25,000 to @PACER_NBPC to help their cause.|author=Life is Strange|date=25 Jan 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2016, [[Legendary Entertainment|Legendary Digital Studios]] and Square Enix announced that they would be adapting ''Life Is Strange'' as a digital series.<ref name=\"adaptation\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/legendary-tackling-adaptation-life-is-914899 |title=Legendary Tackling Adaptation of 'Life Is Strange' Video Game (Exclusive) |first=Borys |last=Kit |date=27 July 2016 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=27 July 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160728134633/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/legendary-tackling-adaptation-life-is-914899 |archivedate=28 July 2016  }}</ref> At the time of the announcement, they were meeting with potential writers for the series adaptation, which would be set in Arcadia Bay.<ref name=\"writers\">{{cite web|url=https://www.legendary.com/legendary-digital-studios-partners-with-square-enix-and-dj2-to-adapt-award-winning-episodic-videogame-life-is-strange-into-digital-series/|title=Legendary Digital Studios Partners with Square Enix and dj2 to Adapt Award Winning Episodic Videogame Life Is Strange into Digital Series|date=27 July 2016|work=[[Legendary Entertainment]]|accessdate=30 July 2016|archivedate=1 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170601063430/https://www.legendary.com/legendary-digital-studios-partners-with-square-enix-and-dj2-to-adapt-award-winning-episodic-videogame-life-is-strange-into-digital-series/|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In 2017, dj2 Entertainment sold the rights to the series to streaming service [[Hulu]].<ref name=\"Deadline\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/europacorp-tv-studios-option-ruiner-video-game-dj2-1202223370/|title=Europacorp TV Studios Options \u2018Ruiner\u2019 Video Game; DJ2 To Produce|first=Erik|last=Pedersen|date=11 December 2017|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|archivedate=12 December 2017|archiveurl=http://archive.today/2017.12.12-174622/http://deadline.com/2017/12/europacorp-tv-studios-option-ruiner-video-game-dj2-1202223370/|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Life Is Strange: Before the Storm]]'', a prequel developed by [[Deck Nine]], launched on 31 August 2017.<ref name=\"b3f0r3th35t0rm\">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/e3/2017/6/11/15779506/life-is-strange-prequel-before-the-storm-release-date|title=Life is Strange prequel Before the Storm debuts this summer (update)|first=Samit|last=Sarkar|date=11 June 2017|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|archivedate=12 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170612033310/https://www.polygon.com/e3/2017/6/11/15779506/life-is-strange-prequel-before-the-storm-release-date|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> A free [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] called ''[[The Awesome Adventures of Captain Spirit]]'' was announced and released in June 2018.<ref name=\"The Verge\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/6/10/17446874/the-awesome-adventures-of-captain-spirit-release-date-life-is-strange |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180610210842/https://www.theverge.com/2018/6/10/17446874/the-awesome-adventures-of-captain-spirit-release-date-life-is-strange |title=New Life is Strange game, The Awesome Adventures of Captain Spirit, coming June 26th |last=Farokhmanesh |first=Megan |website=[[The Verge]] |date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=10 June 2018 |archivedate=10 June 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Engadget\">{{cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2018/06/10/life-is-strange-awesome-adventures-captain-spirit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180610211011/https://www.engadget.com/2018/06/10/life-is-strange-awesome-adventures-captain-spirit/ |title='Life is Strange' returns with 'The Awesome Adventures of Captain Spirit' |last=Summers |first=Nick |website=[[Engadget]] |date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=10 June 2018 |archivedate=10 June 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Polygon\">{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/e3/2018/6/10/17446838/the-awesome-adventures-of-captain-spirit-microsoft-e3-2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180610211015/https://www.polygon.com/e3/2018/6/10/17446838/the-awesome-adventures-of-captain-spirit-microsoft-e3-2018 |title=The Awesome Adventures of Captain Spirit is a \u2018100 percent free\u2019 game in the Life is Strange universe |last=Kuchera |first=Ben |website=[[Polygon (magazine)|Polygon]] |date=10 June 2018 |accessdate=10 June 2018 |archivedate=10 June 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Life Is Strange 2]]'' was released on 27 September 2018,<ref name=\"Phillips-Jun2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-06-22-life-is-strange-2s-first-episode-has-a-release-date|title=Life is Strange 2's first episode has a release date|first=Tom|last=Phillips|date=22 June 2018|website=[[Eurogamer]]}}</ref> featuring a new location and cast of characters.<ref name=\"n3w\">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2015/6/24/8838761/life-is-strange-season-2-new-cast |title=Life is Strange's second season would star a new cast (if it happened) |first=Megan |last=Farokhmanesh |date=24 June 2015 |website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |publisher=[[Vox Media]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161201154029/http://www.polygon.com/2015/6/24/8838761/life-is-strange-season-2-new-cast |archivedate=1 December 2016}}</ref>\n\nA comic book series of the same name, set after the \"Sacrifice Arcadia Bay\" ending of the game, was released by [[Titan Comics]] beginning November 2018.<ref name=\"Knezevic-Mar2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/life-is-strange-comic-series-announced/1100-6457809/|title=Life Is Strange Comic Series Announced|first=Kevin|last=Knezevic|date=29 March 2018|website=[[GameSpot]]|archivedate=30 March 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180330030815/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/life-is-strange-comic-series-announced/1100-6457809/|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Phillips-May2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-05-03-life-is-strange-official-comic-continues-one-of-the-games-endings|title=Life is Strange official comic continues one of the game's endings|first=Tom|last=Phillips|date=3 May 2018|website=[[Eurogamer]]|archivedate=3 May 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180503165127/https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-05-03-life-is-strange-official-comic-continues-one-of-the-games-endings|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Nieves-Jul2018\">{{cite web|url=http://www.comicsbeat.com/sdcc18-titan-finally-gives-more-life-is-strange-details/|title=SDCC\u201918: Titan Finally Announces LIFE IS STRANGE Creative Team Details|first=Davey|last=Nieves|date=21 July 2018|website=[[Comics Beat]]|archivedate=21 July 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180721181157/http://www.comicsbeat.com/sdcc18-titan-finally-gives-more-life-is-strange-details/|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The comic is written by [[Emma Vieceli]], with interior and cover art by Claudia Leonardi and colours by Andrea Izzo.<ref name=\"Nieves-Jul2018\" /> Square Enix also partnered with Titan Comics to produce ''Life Is Strange: Welcome to Blackwell Academy'', a [[tie-in]] book about Blackwell Academy and the town of Arcadia Bay, written by [[Matt Forbeck]].<ref name=\"Riaz-Sep2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hardcoregamer.com/2018/09/03/return-to-arcadia-bay-in-upcoming-life-is-strange-welcome-to-blackwell-academy/311036/|title=Return to Arcadia Bay in Upcoming Life Is Strange: Welcome to Blackwell Academy|first=Adnan|last=Riaz|date=3 September 2018|website=Hardcore Gamer|archivedate=4 September 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20180904110407/https://www.hardcoregamer.com/2018/09/03/return-to-arcadia-bay-in-upcoming-life-is-strange-welcome-to-blackwell-academy/311036/|url-status=live|df=dmy-all|access-date=4 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Speculative fiction|Video games}}\n{{Life Is Strange}}\n{{Dontnod}}\n{{Square Enix franchises}}\n\n{{Good article}}\n\n[[Category:2015 video games]]\n[[Category:Adventure games]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) games]]\n[[Category:Bullying in fiction]]\n[[Category:Cameras in fiction]]\n[[Category:Coming-of-age fiction]]\n[[Category:Video games about dreams]]\n[[Category:Episodic video games]]\n[[Category:Feral Interactive games]]\n[[Category:Interactive movie video games]]\n[[Category:IOS games]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related video games]]\n[[Category:Life Is Strange]]\n[[Category:Linux games]]\n[[Category:MacOS games]]\n[[Category:Mental illness in fiction]]\n[[Category:Fiction about murder]]\n[[Category:Video games about the paranormal]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 3 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation Network games]]\n[[Category:Video games about psychic powers]]\n[