January 2015|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=10 March 2015|archivedate=2 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150202002140/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/01/29/life-strange-episode-1-review-chrysalis|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"character 2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/life-is-strange-review/ |title=Life Is Strange |first=Phil |last=Savage |date=22 October 2015 |work=[[PC Gamer]] |accessdate=22 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151023185424/http://www.pcgamer.com/life-is-strange-review/ |archivedate=23 October 2015  }}</ref> and time travel component,<ref name=\"sleeper hit\" /><ref name=\"time travel 1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/01/29/review-life-is-strange-episode-1-chrysalis/132228/|title=Review: Life is Strange Episode 1: Chrysalis|first=Geoff|last=Thew|date=29 January 2015|work=Hardcore Gamer|accessdate=10 March 2015|archivedate=31 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150131002234/http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/01/29/review-life-is-strange-episode-1-chrysalis/132228/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"time travel 2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.shacknews.com/article/91829/life-is-strange-review-selfie-destruction |title=Life is Strange review: 'Selfie'-destruction |first=Ozzie |last=Mejia |date=21 October 2015 |work=[[Shacknews]] |accessdate=21 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151023164732/http://www.shacknews.com/article/91829/life-is-strange-review-selfie-destruction |archivedate=23 October 2015  }}</ref> suggesting that there should be more games like it.<ref name=\"suggest 2\">{{cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2015/01/life-is-strange-episode-one-review-trying-and-retrying-new-things/ |title=Life is Strange Episode One review: Trying and retrying new things |first=Steven |last=Strom |date=30 January 2015 |work=[[Ars Technica]] |accessdate=22 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022231404/http://arstechnica.com/gaming/2015/01/life-is-strange-episode-one-review-trying-and-retrying-new-things/ |archivedate=22 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name=\"suggest 1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/01/29/review-life-is-strange-episode-1-chrysalis/132228/|title=Review: Life is Strange Episode 1: Chrysalis|first=Geoff|last=Thew|date=29 January 2015|work=Hardcore Gamer|accessdate=21 July 2015|archivedate=31 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150131002234/http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/01/29/review-life-is-strange-episode-1-chrysalis/132228/|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Eurogamer]]'' said it was \"one of the best interactive story games of this generation\"<ref name=\"full season\">{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2015-10-22-life-is-strange |title=Life is Strange review |first=Aoife |last=Wilson |date=22 October 2015 |work=[[Eurogamer]] |accessdate=22 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022200126/http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2015-10-22-life-is-strange |archivedate=22 October 2015  }}</ref> and ''Hardcore Gamer'' said it was the [[sleeper hit]] of 2015.<ref name=\"sleeper hit\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/11/07/review-life-is-strange/175508/|title=Review: Life Is Strange|last=Riaz|first=Adnan|date=7 November 2015|work=Hardcore Gamer|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151108212519/http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/11/07/review-life-is-strange/175508/|archivedate=8 November 2015|url-status=live|accessdate=7 November 2015}}</ref> ''Life Is Strange'' received over 75 Game of the Year awards and listings.<ref name=\"writers\" /> In April 2017, ''Xbox One UK'' ranked it first in its list of Xbox One games priced under {{GB\u00a3|20}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xboxoneuk.com/xbox-one/xbouks-top-20-games-for-under-20|title=XBOUK's Top 20 Games For Under \u00a320|first=Stephen|last=Loftus|date=25 April 2017|website=Xbox One UK|archivedate=1 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170601063704/http://www.xboxoneuk.com/xbox-one/best-20-xbox-one-games-for-under-20/|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Game director [[Yoko Taro]] listed it as one of his favourite PlayStation 4 games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.us.playstation.com/2017/07/11/discover-the-creators-yoko-taros-favorite-ps4-games/|title=Discover the Creators: Yoko Taro's Favorite PS4 Games|author=[[Yoko Taro|Taro, Yoko]]|date=11 July 2017|website=[[PlayStation Blog]]|archivedate=11 July 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170711163205/https://blog.us.playstation.com/2017/07/11/discover-the-creators-yoko-taros-favorite-ps4-games/|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n[[File:GDC 2016 awards 16-20 52 32-01-7D1 0959 (25731583212).jpg|thumb|left|The developers accept the audience award at the 2016 [[Game Developers Choice Awards|GDC Awards]].]]\nKevin VanOrd of ''[[GameSpot]]'' said ''Episode 1: Chrysalis''{{efn|The subtitle ''Chrysalis'' alludes to the [[Pupa#Chrysalis|transitional stage]] of butterflies as pupae, before they emerge into [[Butterfly|adulthood]].<ref name=\"note3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/life-strange-episode-one-review-square-enix-gambles-female-protagonists-1801178|title='Life Is Strange' Episode One Review: Square Enix Gambles With Female Protagonists|first=Vincent|last=Balestriere|date=31 January 2015|work=[[International Business Times]]|accessdate=31 January 2015|archivedate=3 February 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203032128/http://www.ibtimes.com/life-strange-episode-one-review-square-enix-gambles-female-protagonists-1801178|url-status=live}}</ref>}} is \"an involving [[slice of life]] that works because its situations eloquently capture a peculiar early-college state of mind\",<ref name=\"slice of life\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-one-review/1900-6416015/ |title=Life is Strange, Episode One Review |first=Kevin |last=VanOrd |date=29 January 2015 |work=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151024065018/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-one-review/1900-6416015/ |archivedate=24 October 2015  }}</ref> while ''[[Game Informer]]''{{'}}s Kimberley Wallace said the game's tackling of \"subjects that are usually [[taboo]] for video games\" was impressive.<ref name=\"taboo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/life_is_strange/b/pc/archive/2015/01/29/life-is-strange-episode-one-chrysalis-review-game-informer.aspx |title=A Promising And Exciting Debut |first=Kimberley |last=Wallace |date=29 January 2015 |work=[[Game Informer]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151020151045/http://www.gameinformer.com/games/life_is_strange/b/pc/archive/2015/01/29/life-is-strange-episode-one-chrysalis-review-game-informer.aspx |archivedate=20 October 2015  }}</ref> ''[[Destructoid]]''{{'}}s Brett Makedonski said the episode's strongest characteristic was exploration\u2014both \"[[self]]- and worldly\".<ref name=\"self- and worldly\">{{cite web|url=http://www.destructoid.com/review-life-is-strange-chrysalis-286926.phtml |title=Review: Life is Strange: Chrysalis |first=Brett |last=Makedonski |date=29 January 2015 |work=[[Destructoid]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151108031815/http://www.destructoid.com/review-life-is-strange-chrysalis-286926.phtml |archivedate=8 November 2015  }}</ref> Mitch Dyer of ''[[IGN]]'' said the story was ultimately obstructed by its \"laughable\" script and \"worse performances\".<ref name=\"obstruct\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2015/02/02/life-is-strange-episode-1-review |title=Life is Strange: Episode 1 Review |first=Mitch |last=Dyer |date=2 February 2015 |work=[[IGN]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151025110238/http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/02/02/life-is-strange-episode-1-review |archivedate=25 October 2015  }}</ref> In response to ''Episode 2: Out of Time'', ''[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]''{{'}}s Megan Farokhmanesh also said that the emphasis on self-exploration had considerable impact on the enjoyment of the game.<ref name=\"self-exploration\">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/3/25/8291203/life-is-strange-episode-two-review |title=Life is Strange: Episode Two \u2013 Out of Time review: stand by me |first1=Megan |last1=Farokhmanesh |first2=Colin |last2=Campbell |date=25 March 2015 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151226163422/http://www.polygon.com/2015/3/25/8291203/life-is-strange-episode-two-review |archivedate=26 December 2015  }}</ref> Other critics said the ending was an \"emotional high point\" and that it brought meaning to the choices from both the first and second episodes.<ref name=\"emotional high point\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-two-review/1900-6416079/ |title=Life is Strange, Episode Two Review |first=Alexa Ray |last=Corriea |date=26 March 2015 |work=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016054649/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-two-review/1900-6416079/ |archivedate=16 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name=\"meaning\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2015/03/24/life-is-strange-episode-2-review |title=Life is Strange: Episode 2 Review |first=Mitch |last=Dyer |date=24 March 2015 |work=[[IGN]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151030235124/http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/03/24/life-is-strange-episode-2-review |archivedate=30 October 2015  }}</ref> Mike Williams said in ''USgamer'' that the pacing of ''Episode 2: Out of Time'' was \"slower and less exciting\" than that of episode one.<ref name=\"disparaged\">{{cite web|url=http://www.usgamer.net/articles/life-is-strange-episode-2-ps4-review |title=Life is Strange, Episode 2 PS4 Review: The Magical and The Mundane |first=Mike |last=Williams |date=27 March 2015 |work=[[Eurogamer#Subsidiaries|USgamer]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117155701/http://www.usgamer.net/articles/life-is-strange-episode-2-ps4-review |archivedate=17 November 2015  }}</ref>\n\nAdnan Riaz of ''Hardcore Gamer'' said ''Episode 3: Chaos Theory'' was a dramatic improvement that presented a \"thrilling, poignant, fascinating and&nbsp;... enticing\" narrative whose outcome from past decisions also added a sense of realism.<ref name=\"enticing\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/05/22/review-life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory/149654/ |title=Review: Life Is Strange Episode 3: Chaos Theory |first=Adnan |last=Riaz |date=22 May 2015 |work=Hardcore Gamer |accessdate=30 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117031924/http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/05/22/review-life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory/149654/ |archivedate=17 November 2015  }}</ref> Peter Paras of ''[[Game Revolution]]'' complimented the character beats, particularly the development of Chloe Price, who he said \"really comes into her own as [a] fully-formed character\".<ref name=\"fully-formed\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory |title=Life Is Strange: Episode 3 \u2013 Chaos Theory Review |first=Peter |last=Paras |date=19 May 2015 |work=[[Game Revolution]] |accessdate=30 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151012041001/http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory |archivedate=12 October 2015  }}</ref> Though ''GameSpot''{{'}}s Alexa Ray Corriea said that the [[Quest (video gaming)#Gather quests|fetch quests]] interfered with its emotional quality,<ref name=\"interfere\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-three-review/1900-6416147/ |title=Life is Strange, Episode Three Review |first=Alexa Ray |last=Corriea |date=20 May 2015 |work=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151102040010/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-three-review/1900-6416147/ |archivedate=2 November 2015  }}</ref> the episode built up to a \"killer cliffhanger\" according to Farokhmanesh.<ref name=\"killer\">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/6/1/8688317/life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory-review |title=Life is Strange: Episode Three \u2013 Chaos Theory review: echo chamber |first1=Megan |last1=Farokhmanesh |first2=Colin |last2=Campbell |date=1 June 2015 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018115049/http://www.polygon.com/2015/6/1/8688317/life-is-strange-episode-3-chaos-theory-review |archivedate=18 October 2015  }}</ref> ''GameZone''{{'}}s Matt Liebl said ''Episode 4: Dark Room'' was \"easily the most emotional episode\" and that the mystery of Rachel Amber had done a \"tremendous job in keeping us hooked\".<ref name=\"mystery\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamezone.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-4-dark-room-review-jv9v |title=Life is Strange Episode 4: Dark Room Review |first=Matt |last=Liebl |date=30 July 2015 |work=GameZone |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151023163037/http://www.gamezone.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-4-dark-room-review-jv9v |archivedate=23 October 2015  }}</ref> Tom Hoggins of ''[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]'' said the developer's venture into subjects like [[Social class|social division]], [[Cyberbullying|online bullying]], parental conflict and [[suicide]] as \"bold\".<ref name=\"bold\">{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/gaming/what-to-play/life-is-strange-episode-4-review/ |title=Life is Strange, Episode 4, The Dark Room: 'Precariously balanced' |first=Tom |last=Hoggins |date=11 August 2015 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151015013926/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/gaming/what-to-play/life-is-strange-episode-4-review/ |archivedate=15 October 2015  }}</ref> Critics said there were [[Tone (literature)|tonal]] problems, caused by the game's \"cheap ways\" of progressing the plot, such as character inconsistency and superfluous [[shock value]].<ref name=\"cheap 1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2015/07/30/life-is-strange-episode-4-dark-room-review |title=Life Is Strange \u2013 Episode 4: Dark Room Review |first=Mitch |last=Dyer |date=30 July 2015 |work=[[IGN]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151102014136/http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/07/30/life-is-strange-episode-4-dark-room-review |archivedate=2 November 2015  }}</ref><ref name=\"cheap 2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-four-review/1900-6416204/ |title=Life is Strange, Episode Four Review |first=Alexa Ray |last=Corriea |date=28 July 2015 |work=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151028230540/http://www.gamespot.com/reviews/life-is-strange-episode-four-review/1900-6416204/ |archivedate=28 October 2015  }}</ref> Critics were more favourable towards the episode's puzzles and relationships.<ref name=\"puzzles\">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/8/13/9130223/life-is-strange-episode-4-review-dark-room |title=Life is Strange: Episode Four \u2013 Dark Room review: low road |first1=Megan |last1=Farokhmanesh |first2=Colin |last2=Campbell |date=13 August 2015 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151024070210/http://www.polygon.com/2015/8/13/9130223/life-is-strange-episode-4-review-dark-room |archivedate=24 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name=\"relationships\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/life-is-strange--episode-4-the-dark-room |title=Life Is Strange \u2013 Episode 4: The Dark Room Review |first=Peter |last=Paras |date=6 August 2015 |work=[[Game Revolution]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117020622/http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/life-is-strange--episode-4-the-dark-room |archivedate=17 November 2015  }}</ref> They said the final episode, ''Polarized'', had a \"fitting conclusion\" to the [[coming of age]] story of Max Caulfield and the relationship between the two leads was carried out successfully.<ref name=\"of age\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/10/26/review-life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized/173583/ |title=Review: Life Is Strange Episode 5: Polarized |first=Adnan |last=Riaz |date=26 October 2015 |work=Hardcore Gamer |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151028195126/http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/10/26/review-life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized/173583/ |archivedate=28 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name=\"two leads\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/life_is_strange_episode_5_-_polarized/b/playstation4/archive/2015/10/21/life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized-review-game-informer.aspx |title=Life is Strange: Episode 5 \u2013 Polarized |first=Kimberley |last=Wallace |date=21 October 2015 |work=[[Game Informer]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151030031739/http://www.gameinformer.com/games/life_is_strange_episode_5_-_polarized/b/playstation4/archive/2015/10/21/life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized-review-game-informer.aspx |archivedate=30 October 2015  }}</ref> One stealth sequence was described as \"tedious\" and \"out-of-place\" while other aspects inhabiting the same course of events were favoured.<ref name=\"tedious\">{{cite web|url=http://www.themarysue.com/life-really-is-strange/ |title=Review: Life Is Strange Episode 5: \"Polarized\" AKA Let's Have a Feels Trip |first=Jessica |last=Lachenal |date=21 October 2015 |work=[[Dan Abrams#The Mary Sue|The Mary Sue]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151024003355/http://www.themarysue.com/life-really-is-strange/ |archivedate=24 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name=\"out-of-place\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2015/10/22/life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized-review |title=Life Is Strange \u2013 Episode 5: Polarized Review |first=Mitch |last=Dyer |date=21 October 2015 |work=[[IGN]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151104092509/http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/10/22/life-is-strange-episode-5-polarized-review |archivedate=4 November 2015  }}</ref> Reviewers were divided on the ending.<ref name=\"good 2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.usgamer.net/articles/life-is-strange-episode-5-review |title=Life is Strange Episode 5 PS4 Review: Time to Let Things Go |first=Mike |last=Williams |date=23 October 2015 |work=[[Eurogamer#Subsidiaries|USgamer]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151027235637/http://www.usgamer.net/articles/life-is-strange-episode-5-review |archivedate=27 October 2015  }}</ref><ref name=\"good 1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/10/21/9589174/life-is-strange-episode-5-review-polarized |title=Life is Strange: Episode Five \u2013 Polarized review |first1=Megan |last1=Farokhmanesh |first2=Colin |last2=Campbell |date=21 October 2015 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=31 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151029223907/http://www.polygon.com/2015/10/21/9589174/life-is-strange-episode-5-review-polarized |