date=25 July 2015  }}</ref> having accumulated over 1.2 million unique players worldwide; the [[attach rate]] to units between the complete season and [[Season ticket#Other uses|season pass]] proved to be \"extremely strong\", divulged Square Enix.<ref name=\"unique players\">{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/7/23/9022561/life-is-strange-episode-4-release-date-trailer |title=Life is Strange hits 1M copies sold, fourth episode coming next week |first=Samit |last=Sarkar |date=23 July 2015 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |accessdate=24 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725015350/http://www.polygon.com/2015/7/23/9022561/life-is-strange-episode-4-release-date-trailer |archivedate=25 July 2015  }}</ref> The retail edition made seventh place in the top ten [[United Kingdom|UK]] game sales chart for the week ending 23 January 2016.<ref name=\"uk sales\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/call-of-duty-black-ops-3-camps-at-top-of-uk-chart/1100-6434106/ |title=Call of Duty: Black Ops 3 Camps at Top of UK Chart |first=Tamoor |last=Hussain |date=25 January 2016 |work=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=26 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160128033016/http://www.gamespot.com/articles/call-of-duty-black-ops-3-camps-at-top-of-uk-chart/1100-6434106/ |archivedate=28 January 2016  }}</ref> ''Life Is Strange'' was one of the top 100 best-selling games on Steam in 2016.<ref name=\"dry ice\">{{cite web|url=http://store.steampowered.com/sale/2016_top_sellers/ |title=Top 100 |website=[[Steam (software)|Steam]] |publisher=[[Valve Corporation|Valve]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170102152559/http://store.steampowered.com/sale/2016_top_sellers/ |archivedate=2 January 2017  }}</ref> As of May 2017, more than three million copies have been sold.<ref name=\"c0p135\">{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-05-18-life-is-strange-2-finally-confirmed |title=Life is Strange 2 finally confirmed |first=Tom |last=Phillips |date=18 May 2017 |website=[[Eurogamer]] |publisher=[[Gamer Network]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170518213403/http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-05-18-life-is-strange-2-finally-confirmed |archivedate=18 May 2017  }}</ref><ref name=\"1nth3w0rk5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.destructoid.com/a-new-life-is-strange-game-is-in-the-works-436830.phtml|title=A new Life is Strange game is in the works|first=Ray|last=Porreca|date=18 May 2017|website=[[Destructoid]]|publisher=[[ModernMethod]]|archivedate=1 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170601064007/https://www.destructoid.com/a-new-life-is-strange-game-is-in-the-works-436830.phtml|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Awards===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible\"\n|- valign=\"bottom\"\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Recipient(s) and nominee(s) !! Result !! class=\"unsortable\" | Ref.\n|- valign=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"25\"|2015\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Develop (magazine)|Develop Industry Excellence Awards]]\n| New Games IP \u2013 PC/console\n| rowspan=\"5\"|''Life Is Strange''\n| {{Won}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"|<ref name=\"develop awards\">{{cite web|url=http://www.develop-online.net/news/develop-awards-2015-the-winners-revealed/0208946 |title=Develop Awards 2015: The winners revealed |first=James |last=Batchelor |date=15 July 2015 |work=[[Develop (magazine)|Develop]] |accessdate=16 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716164603/http://www.develop-online.net/news/develop-awards-2015-the-winners-revealed/0208946 |archivedate=16 July 2015  }}</ref>\n|- valign=\"center\"\n| Use of Narrative\n| {{Won}}\n|- valign=\"center\"\n| rowspan=\"6\"|[[Golden Joystick Award]]s\n| Best Original Game\n| {{Won|place=Silver|Runner-Up}}\n| rowspan=\"6\"|<ref name=\"golden joystick awards\">{{cite web|url=http://www.twitch.tv/goldenjoystickawards/v/23163885 |title=Golden Joystick Awards 2015 |date=30 October 2015